===Etymology===
*A contraction of [[pomegranate]], [[rhyming slang]] for [[immigrant]] ("imme-granate").
*A devolution of "Prisoner of His/Her Majesty" or "POHM"
:''Many folk etymologies also exist.''

===Noun===
'''pom''' ([[poms]])

#(''Australian'', ''pejorative'') An [[Englishman]], A [[Briton]], A person of [[British]] decent.
#:'''Usage Note''': The use of this word to refer to a British person is considered pejorative. The word is, however, used by some British people as a neutral or even affirmative term. When used by someone who is not British, it is almost invariably considered offensive

